## Overview

The **AI-Powered Resume Screener** is an end-to-end ML system that automates candidate shortlisting for HR teams. It combines **BERT semantic embeddings** with **TF-IDF keyword matching** to score and rank resumes against a job description — surfacing the most relevant candidates with an explainable confidence score.

```
Upload JD + Resumes  →  NLP Scoring Engine  →  Ranked Shortlist  →  Export CSV
```

### Why this project?

| Problem | Solution |
|---------|----------|
| HR teams spend ~23 hrs/hire on resume review | Automated scoring in seconds |
| Inconsistent manual evaluation | Consistent, bias-aware ML scoring |
| Missed qualified candidates | Semantic matching beyond keyword search |
| Unscalable for 500+ applications | Async batch processing via FastAPI |

